cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper deals with learning with hidden variables, which is a central challenge in probabilistic graphical models. This topic is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that cs.LG and cs.AI are likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the Information Bottleneck principle, which is a concept from information theory, indicating that cs.IT is another likely sub-category. The paper's focus on tradeoffs between objectives and convergence on high-scoring solutions suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
